\begin_layout Section
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Explaining the remarkable diversity in sex-determining mechanisms has been
 a long-standing question in evolutionary biology 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Bull1983,Uller2011,Beukeboom2014,Bachtrog2014"

\end_inset

.
 Indeed, numerous models have been developed to explain transitions between
 different sex-determining mechanisms in animals and plants (e.g., 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citealp
key "Bull1981b,Bulmer1982,Pomiankowski2004,Doorn2007,Kuijper2010a,Kuijper2014"

\end_inset

, reviewed in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citealp
key "Doorn2014"

\end_inset

).
 By contrast, groups like fungi, ciliates or slime molds have received much
 less attention: existing models exclusively focus on the evolution of gametic
 dimorphism (
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "hadjivasiliou2015cell,Hadjivasiliou2013"

\end_inset

), and the number of sexes, or `mating types' (e.g., 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citealp
key "Charlesworth1979a,Iwasa1987,Hurst1996a,Perrin2012"

\end_inset

; reviewed in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citealp
key "Billiard2011"

\end_inset

), whereas few predictions exist about evolutionary transitions between
 different forms of mating-type determination 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Paixao2011"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Particularly interesting is the repeated evolution of mating-type switching,
 where mating type identity changes between parents and offspring or later
 descendants.
 For example, in some members of the ciliate genus 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
emph{Paramecium}
\end_layout

\end_inset

, mating type is the result of the cytoplasmic transmission of small RNAs
 over several clonal cell divisions 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Sawka2012,Singh2014"

\end_inset

.
 These small RNAs modulate the expression of genetically inherited mating
 type alleles in the micronucleus, causing only the maternally inherited
 allele to be expressed 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Singh2014,Bloomfield2014"

\end_inset

.
 Interestingly, the transmission of mating type expression can switch between
 generations, dependent on environmental stimuli such as cycles of light
 and darkness and temperature 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Barnett1966,Taub1966"

\end_inset

.
 In another ciliate, 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
emph{Tetrahymena}
\end_layout

\end_inset

, mating type is determined stochastically at sex, so that individual cells
 switch between one of 7 adjacent mating type alleles through recombination
 each generation 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Paixao2011,Cervantes2013"

\end_inset

.
 In fungi, mating-type switching has been found in the basidiomycete 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
emph{Agrocybe aegerita}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Labarere1992"

\end_inset

 and has evolved independently in the ascomycete budding yeast 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
emph{Saccharomyces cerevisiae}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 (and sister species: 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citealp
key "Hanson2014"

\end_inset

) and fission yeast 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
emph{Schizosaccharomyces pombe}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Klar2007"

\end_inset

.
 In these yeasts, individuals contain at least one copy of both mating type
 alleles, but only express one allele due to a variety of mechanisms such
 as ectopic recombination and epigenetic silencing 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
before "reviewed in"
key "Klar2007,Haber2012,Hanson2014"

\end_inset

.
 Finally, we note that despite recent progress 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
before "e.g.,"
key "Beukeboom2014"

\end_inset

, the sexual lives of many other unicellular eukaryotes remain unknown,
 so more instances of mating type switching are likely to be found in the
 future.
 
